Tip added by Legend: Silencia<br><br>
<h3>Grouping with Rogues </h3></b></center></font>
<br>
<center>
<table bgcolor="black" text="silver" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="1" width="95%">

<td align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="black">
<center>

<table bgcolor="black" text="silver" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="1" width="95%">

<tr><td align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="black">

<font face="arial" Size="-1" color="caffb0"><b>When you group with a rogue, and you are a melee, ALWAYS stay opposite the rogue. If the rogue constantly has to switch sides or move around backstabbing is harder to do. All tanks should stand side-by-side. Also if the caster has a pet and the pet is meleeing, stand beside that pet. It is harder for the caster to move the pet then it is for you to move. Thank you.


Silencia Shadowstealer
Redeemed Rogue of 37 Seasons
</b><br></font>
<br><br>

</td></tr>



